        "summary": "Create an offer to deliver cloud services to your tenants.",
        "longSummary": "Your tenants subscribe to offers. Create offers to reflect different billing models that your tenants can opt into. Each offer can have default quotas and opt-in quotas.",
        "description": "<p>Tenants subscribe to offers. Offers can be private or publicly visible to the tenants. Offers can have both base plans and add-on plans; base plans determine default quotas available to the tenant subscription, while add-on plans are opt-in for the tenant at a later time.</p>\r\nCommon Offers:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Pay-as-you-go  To charge your customers for only what they use, create a plan with maximum quota limits for each cloud service, and add it as a base plan for the offer. Tenants will be able to use up to their quota and can be charged based on their subscriptions usage data.</li>\r\n<li>Pre-paid  Include base plans with any default quotas to be provided to the tenant as part of subscribing to the offer. Use add-on plans to offer services that can be added at a later time.</li>\r\n<li>Private offers  To create an offer for a specific tenant that is not visible to other tenants, create the personalized offer and keep it in a private state. You assign tenant subscriptions instead of providing it through self-service sign up.</li>\r\n</ul>",
