        "summary": "Assign regions and quotas for your cloud services in a plan to offer to your tenants.",
        "longSummary": "Plans bundle cloud services together to be offered to tenants. A plan can always be modified at a later time to add additional services or modify quotas for any service.",
        "description": "<p>When creating a plan, you must select which cloud services will be made available to the tenant within the plan. For each service selected, you also can specify which regions the service will be available in and what limits will be applied on consumption of the service (quotas).</p> \r\n   <p> Plans are then made available to tenants by including them in offers. The base plans of an offer determine default quotas available to the tenant subscription, while add-on plans are opt-in for the tenant at a later time. </p>\r\n   <p> Not seeing a service that you want to offer? Make sure to register and configure at least one region of each resource provider that you wish to include in your plans.</p>",
